column5: hers some of the jumbos i caught on new moon last week and old faithful...the micro jigging rap  including one canibal...lol... i think perch pattern is my new go to for perch?

solid fry up right there!  I read an interesting article a while back that suggest many fish become cannibals once they reach a certain size...something to do with proteins being the same, as compared to non cannibalized prey, and therefore more growth/nutrition..something like that anyways...I think it was a euro researched paper, mainly talking about pike and zander...if i can find it again i'll post it..very interesting read
ended up with 5.5 pounds from 35 perch!
Is that the famous lancaster perch Mike ? they taste like candy .Some of them are real monsters too !!!  Paul
Long sault... 30 minutes west of the famous Lancaster but just as tasty... And lots over 10"
On my last perching trip the Perch designed Salmo Chubby darter produced the biggest fish.  Nice pull....lots of meat from those fish!
